```json
{
  "application": "GROMACS",
  "details": {
    "version": "2021.4",
    "resources": {
      "nodes": 1,
      "cpus": 64,
      "mpi_processes": 64,
      "memory": "10GB",
      "walltime": "05:00:00",
      "queue": "short_cpuQ",
      "OMP_NUM_THREADS": 1
    },
    "script_description": "This script runs a molecular dynamics simulation using GROMACS. It uses 64 MPI processes and 1 thread per process. The simulation is run for 5 hours with a memory limit of 10GB. The script is submitted to the 'short_cpuQ' queue. The output is written to 'logs/wt2_rep0_out' and errors are written to 'logs/wt2_rep0_err'.",
    "script_commands": [
      "module load gromacs-2021.4",
      "export OMP_NUM_THREADS=1",
      "cd $PBS_O_WORKDIR/../wt2_rep0/4_MD",
      "mpirun -np 64 gmx_mpi mdrun -cpi md_plain -v -deffnm md_plain"
    ]
  }
}
```
